# .worktreeinclude — gitignored files copied into each new Claude Code worktree.
#
# Uses .gitignore syntax. A file is copied only when it BOTH matches a pattern
# here AND is gitignored AND actually exists — tracked files are never
# duplicated, and missing files are silently skipped (so unused patterns no-op).
# Docs: https://code.claude.com/docs/en/worktrees#copy-gitignored-files-into-worktrees
#
# The patterns below mirror the secret conventions in this repo's .gitignore, so a
# new worktree inherits whatever local env/credential files you already have and can
# run the dev server, seed scripts, and Firebase Admin tooling without re-setup.
#
# NOT copied on purpose: node_modules/ (large — run `npm install` per worktree)
# and generated/build artifacts (.next/, out/, scripts/bundles-output/, etc. —
# regenerated by the build/seed scripts).

# Local environment files (Next.js reads .env.local / .env.* at build & runtime)
.env
.env.local
.env.*
!.env.example

# Firebase / Google service-account & credential keys (mirrors .gitignore)
service-account*.json
serviceAccountKey*.json
firebase-admin*.json
google-credentials*.json
gcp-credentials*.json
credentials.json
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
